According to Hoeffding's inequality, 
$$ P(|x-p|>\epsilon) \leq 2e^{-2n\epsilon ^2} $$
Given $\delta = 0.05$, 
$$ 2e^{-2n\epsilon^2} < 0.05 $$
$$ e^{-2n\epsilon^2} < 0.025 $$
$$ -2n\epsilon^2 < \ln(0.025) $$
$$ \epsilon^2 > \frac {-\ln(0.025)} {2n} $$
$$ \epsilon > \sqrt \frac {-\ln(0.025)} {2n} $$

Since we want $\epsilon$ to be as tight as possible, we will choose $\epsilon$ to be exactly $\sqrt \frac {-\ln(0.025)} {2n}$. 